message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Gambia, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you have the time, walking can be a good option. It will take you approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, cycling can be a faster and more convenient option. It will take you around 5-10 minutes to reach the grocery store.

3. Public Transportation: Depending on the availability, you can check if there are any local buses or minibusses (known as "gele-gele" or "sept-place") that pass by or near the grocery store. This can be a cost-effective option, but the frequency and reliability of public transportation may vary.

4. Taxi: Taxis are readily available in Gambia, and you can easily find one to take you to the grocery store. It will be a quick and convenient option, but it may be relatively more expensive compared to other modes of transportation.

Consider your budget, time constraints, and personal preferences when choosing the best mode of transportation to reach the grocery store.
